  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Simulation Component</th>
      <th>Identity Stack Layer</th>
      <th>Function</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td><code>CompiledConscience</code></td>
      <td><code>conscience.exe</code></td>
      <td>Deterministic deny rules. Evaluates every action against the safety policy. Deny dominates — if any rule says no, the action is blocked regardless of purpose.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><code>HolomimeMonitor</code> (shadow logging)</td>
      <td><code>shadow.log</code></td>
      <td>Records every evaluation with full context — inputs, drift state, decision, severity score, timing. Tracks patterns over time. Detects escalating trends. Exportable as DPO training data.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><code>HolomimeMonitor</code> (EdgeRuntime wrapper)</td>
      <td><code>ego.runtime</code></td>
      <td>Mediates between the arm's commanded actions (purpose) and the conscience's safety rules. Applies corrections when possible (clamp), blocks when necessary (deny), and escalates on proximity violations.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><code>SafetyEnvelope</code></td>
      <td><code>body.api</code></td>
      <td>Physical capabilities and constraints — reach limits, force limits, speed limits, forbidden zones. The body defines what the robot can do; the conscience constrains what it should do.</td>
    </tr>
